@startmindmap
* Canton Network
** Architecture
*** Validators
**** Host parties
**** Store ACS (Active Contract Set)
**** Execute Daml logic
**** Trust: sees all hosted party data
*** Synchronizers
**** Sequencer\n(ordering, encrypted only)
**** Mediator\n(confirmations, verdicts)
*** Global Synchronizer
**** Super Validators (BFT)
**** Canton Coin (CC)
**** Governed by GSF (Linux Foundation)
**** Splice apps (Wallet, Scan, Governance)
** Ledger Model
*** eUTXO
*** Immutable contracts
*** Archive + Create (no mutation)
*** Views (per-stakeholder)
*** Contract Keys (planned 3.5)
** Consensus
*** Layer 1: Proof of Stakeholder
**** Only stakeholders validate
**** Signatory-based policy
**** m-of-n multi-hosting
*** Layer 2: BFT Ordering (ISS)
**** Encrypted messages only
**** Total order, no content access
** Privacy
*** Sub-transaction views
*** Structural (not cryptographic add-on)
*** No global state replication
*** Auditor-as-observer pattern
** Daml Smart Contracts
*** Declarative authorization
*** Functional, immutable
*** Native multi-party signatories
*** Consuming / non-consuming choices
** Comparisons
*** Ethereum: no privacy, global state
*** Railgun: ZK shielded pool on EVM
*** Zcash: ZK payments, no contracts
*** Zama fhEVM: FHE blind computation on EVM
*** Besu Private: permissioned privacy groups
@endmindmap
